# Privacy Policy — GTF Bot (GKS Tychy Fanatics)

Last updated: 2026-07-16

This Privacy Policy explains what data the **GTF Bot**  collects and
processes on the **GKS Tychy Fanatics** Discord server, how that
data gets used, and what rights you have over it.

By using the Server and/or the Bot, you're agreeing to what's below.

## 1. Who's responsible for your data

The person running the Server and the Bot acts as the data controller.

For anything data-related, reach out at:
**blokxx.ts@gmail.com**

## 2. What gets collected

The Bot runs on Discord's official API and only touches what it actually
needs to do its job. Depending on which features you use, that can include:

- **Basic Discord account info** — your user ID, username/tag, avatar,
  account creation date, and when you joined the Server (Discord hands this
  to the Bot automatically through its API).
- **Roles and verification status** — whether you clicked the verification
  button and got the matching role.
- **Support tickets** — whatever you write inside a private ticket channel,
  visible to the mods handling that ticket.
- **Moderation logs** — in a private mod channel, the Bot logs things like
  the content and attachments of deleted messages (this is how it catches
  abuse and helps with moderation), warnings, mutes, kicks and bans, and the
  account age of people joining the Server (an anti-raid check).
- **Permanent ban list** — a user ID plus a reason, kept if someone gets
  permanently banned from the Server.
- **Virtual currency** — a user ID tied to a "balance" used by the Bot's
  fun/economy features (this currency doesn't exist outside the Server —
  see the Terms of Service).
- **Giveaway entries** — whether you entered a giveaway run through the Bot.
- **Music search queries** — whatever you type into `/graj` or similar
  commands (a song title, a link) gets sent to external Lavalink servers and
  services like YouTube so the Bot can find and play it (more on this in
  section 4).

The Bot does **not** collect passwords, payment details, IP addresses, or
anything else unrelated to using Discord.

## 3. Why this data is processed

Only for:

- keeping the Server safe and orderly (moderation, anti-raid, the permanent
  ban list),
- handling user requests through the ticket system,
- verifying new members,
- running the community features (virtual economy, giveaways, match
  commands),
- playing music when someone asks for it,
- keeping the Bot running in general.

## 4. Third parties

The Bot relies on a few external services to work:

- **Discord Inc.** — the platform the Bot runs on, covered by
  [Discord's own Privacy Policy](https://discord.com/privacy).
- **Public Lavalink servers** — independent, external servers used to look
  up and stream audio. These aren't run by the Bot's owner, they change from
  time to time, and there's no full control over them. Song queries (title,
  link) are only sent there to carry out a music command.
- **YouTube / Google** — the source of metadata and audio for music
  commands.
- **Publicly available sports websites** — used to pull GKS Tychy's match
  schedule; no user data is ever sent there.

The owner doesn't sell or hand over user data for marketing purposes.

## 5. How long data is kept

- Operational data (the ban list, ticket counters, virtual economy
  balances, panel messages) stays in the Bot's data files until it's
  manually removed by the owner, or until it's no longer needed (e.g. you
  leave the Server).
- Moderation logs stay in the private mod channel until the Server's admin
  team deletes them.
- Data gets removed promptly on a reasonable request, unless there's a
  legitimate reason to keep it around (an ongoing dispute, an active
  sanction, that sort of thing).

## 6. Legal basis

Data is processed based on:

- legitimate interest (GDPR Art. 6(1)(f)) — keeping the Server and the Bot
  safe and functioning properly,
- consent given by joining the Server and using the Bot's commands
  (GDPR Art. 6(1)(a)).

## 7. Your rights

Under GDPR you can:

- access your data,
- have it corrected,
- have it deleted ("right to be forgotten"),
- restrict how it's processed,
- object to processing,
- request data portability,
- file a complaint with your national data protection authority (in Poland,
  the President of the Personal Data Protection Office — UODO).

To use any of these, email the address in section 1. Leaving the Server and
asking for the archived data (mod logs, economy balance, etc.) to be wiped
covers most of it in practice.

## 8. Data security

Data is kept in files and channels only the Server's admin team can access.
Only people with a moderation/admin role can see it.

## 9. Age requirements

Using Discord — and by extension the Bot — is only allowed under
[Discord's Terms](https://discord.com/terms), which set a minimum age
(generally 13, higher in some countries).

## 10. Changes to this policy

This Policy may change as the Bot evolves. Any major changes will be
announced on the Server. The date at the top of this document reflects the
last update.

